result.execSummary:
The defendant Alanna M Shields-Dominguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court grants 38 days credit if revoked.  Defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Court will allow for transfer to Dane County.

miscConds.notes: AODA assessment, follow through with any treatment recommended.  Comply with random urine screens.  Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia.  No use or possession of CBD products.  No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription.  No use or possession of vaping products.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations. If the Defendant violates any terms of his/her probation, or has any condition time imposed, the Court will deem that the conditions precedent necessary for the conditional grant of Expunction have not been met and therefore Expunction is denied. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.

No contact with co-defendant.

Take Thinking for a Change Course.  Make best efforts to maintain/obtain full time employment, educational plan, or volunteer work.  Attend a minimum of 2 self-help meetings per week in person.

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.
Standard court costs waived.  DNA Surcharge to be paid as a condition of probation.

District Attorney's Office Law Intern Jack Rieder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes a plea questionnaire was filed and inquires how the matter is proceeding.  Atty. Galaviz requests the matter proceed to plea and sentencing today.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Galaviz confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court orders Counts 2 & 3 be dismissed and read in.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Galaviz.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

3 Years Imprisonment (38 Days Credit IF revoked and sentence imposed)
-	1 Year & 6 Months of Initial Confinement
-	1 Year & 6 Months of Extended Supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Term of Probation: 2 Years - Court will allow for transfer to Dane County.

Conditions of Probation/Extended Supervision:
-	No contact with the Co-Defendant.
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of CBD products;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
-	No use of possession of vaping products;
-	Take Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Make best efforts to Maintain/Obtain full time employment, educational plan, or volunteer work;
-	Attend a minimum of 2 self-help meetings per week in person.  

Condition Time: 60 Days STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion (Huber privileges at the Agent's discretion)

FINE or COSTS:  Waived by the Court.

DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  

**Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.**
